## Data protection summary

We process personal data lawfully, fairly and transparently. The lawful bases on which we rely are recorded in the *Record of Processing Activities*. The retention periods are recorded in the *Data Retention Policy*.

Data subjects have rights — access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, objection — which are exercised via the *Subject Access Request Process*. We respond within one month unless an extension is justified and notified to the subject.

## Security summary

- Strong authentication (MFA) for every account that touches customer data, money, or production.
- Encryption at rest and in transit for every system that stores customer data.
- Least-privilege access; access is granted on need, reviewed quarterly, and revoked promptly when an engagement ends.
- Logging and monitoring on every production system, with alerts routed to the on-call rotation.
- An incident response process that the team has practised at least once.

The long form of each of the above is in the *Security Policy*.

## Third parties

We use third parties — software vendors, contractors, advisers — to do work we do not do ourselves. We pick them on the basis of fit, quality and price, in that order.

Every third-party relationship is logged in the *Tool Stack Register* or the *Subscription Cost Register*. The owner of the relationship is the person responsible for renewal, escalation and review. No third party is engaged without a written contract.

## Legal compliance

We comply with the laws of every country in which we operate. Where the laws of two countries conflict, we comply with the stricter and document the reason in the *Decision Log*.

We do not interpret the law informally. Where a question has legal consequence — a contract, a privacy decision, an employment matter — we take advice from a qualified professional. The cost of advice is recorded in the budget; the absence of advice is recorded as a risk.

